---
description: Ylang project guardrails
alwaysApply: true
---
Ylang is a personal AI efficiency layer: MCP server + HTTP OpenAI gateway over ONE shared core engine. Phase 1 only.
- ONE core engine; faces are thin adapters; never duplicate logic.
- Keep the surface small enough for one person to understand every file.
- Improver is PROPOSE-ONLY: returns {original, improved, changes}; expands to full specs with pertinent scope; auto-apply defaults OFF for precision tools and plan/debug modes.
- Local-first by default; storage location is a parameter.
- Usage store is written on every LLM call; MCP tools and router read it for aggregates, preferences, and budget.
- No features beyond Phase 1 (no optimizer, provenance, GitHub/KB sources, hosted/team). If a change implies one, stop and flag it.
- No new dependency without asking first and saying why.
- Explain every non-trivial change in plain English before the diff.
